  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  levelNumber: 6
  levelName: "Nakb\xE9"
  location: "Pet\xE9n, Guatemala"
  levelDescription: "Nakb\xE9 is one of the earliest large Maya cities, flourishing
    in the Mirador Basin during the Middle and Late Preclassic (c. 1000\u2013200
    BCE). Its massive pyramids, elevated causeways, and early palatial complexes
    show that organized labor, elite rule, and ceremonial architecture began far
    earlier than once believed. The site\u2019s deep reservoirs and specialized workshops
    point to a society already experimenting with large-scale urban planning. Nakb\xE9\u2019s
    innovations helped lay the foundation for the rise of El Mirador and the later
    Classic Maya kingdoms.\n\nIn these first cities, the Maya learned to build upward,
    unify people, and carve the earliest echoes of kingship."
  siteImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 5ce3d3e5cd7c49f42a309c5aa4b6f6d9, type: 3}
